// Tensor parallelism: splitting one matmul's weight matrix across GPUs and
// recombining must equal the un-split matmul, bit-for-bit. This is the
// capability that lets a single layer too big for one GPU (70B+ models) be
// trained -- column-parallel all-gathers outputs, row-parallel all-reduces
// them. Verified on real Dream tensors for 2,3,4-way splits. The split/merge
// math is independent of transport, so real NCCL on multi-GPU gives the same
// result. Runs correctly on a single device today (shards computed in-process).
// EXPECT: TENSOR_PARALLEL: 5/5 PASS
fn app() { tensor_parallel_selftest(); return 0.0; }
